<div class="passage-text"><div class='passage-wrap'><div class='passage-content passage-class-0'><div class="version-NIV result-text-style-normal text-html ">
<h1 class="passage-display"> <span class="passage-display-bcv">Matthew 6</span> <span class="passage-display-version">New International Version (NIV)</span></h1> <h3><span id="en-NIV-23284" class="text Matt-6-1">Giving to the Needy</span></h3><p class="chapter-1"><span class="text Matt-6-1"><span class="chapternum">6 </span><span class="woj">“Be careful not to practice your righteousness in front of others to be seen by them.<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23284A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23284A'></sup> If you do, you will have no reward from your Father in heaven.</span></span></p> <p><span id="en-NIV-23285" class="text Matt-6-2"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">2 </sup>“So when you give to the needy, do not announce it with trumpets, as the hypocrites do in the synagogues and on the streets, to be honored by others. Truly I tell you, they have received their reward in full.</span></span> <span id="en-NIV-23286" class="text Matt-6-3"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">3 </sup>But when you give to the needy, do not let your left hand know what your right hand is doing,</span></span> <span id="en-NIV-23287" class="text Matt-6-4"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">4 </sup>so that your giving may be in secret. Then your Father, who sees what is done in secret, will reward you.<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23287B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23287B'></sup></span></span></p> <h3><span id="en-NIV-23288" class="text Matt-6-5">Prayer<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23288C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23288C'></sup></span></h3><p><span class="text Matt-6-5"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">5 </sup>“And when you pray, do not be like the hypocrites, for they love to pray standing<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23288D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23288D'></sup> in the synagogues and on the street corners to be seen by others. Truly I tell you, they have received their reward in full.</span></span> <span id="en-NIV-23289" class="text Matt-6-6"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">6 </sup>But when you pray, go into your room, close the door and pray to your Father,<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23289E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23289E'></sup> who is unseen. Then your Father, who sees what is done in secret, will reward you.</span></span> <span id="en-NIV-23290" class="text Matt-6-7"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">7 </sup>And when you pray, do not keep on babbling<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23290F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23290F'></sup> like pagans, for they think they will be heard because of their many words.<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23290G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23290G'></sup></span></span> <span id="en-NIV-23291" class="text Matt-6-8"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">8 </sup>Do not be like them, for your Father knows what you need<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23291H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23291H'></sup> before you ask him.</span></span></p> <p><span id="en-NIV-23292" class="text Matt-6-9"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">9 </sup>“This, then, is how you should pray:</span></span></p><div class="poetry top-05"><p class="line"><span class="text Matt-6-9"><span class="woj">“‘Our Father<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23292I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23292I'></sup> in heaven,</span></span><br /><span class="text Matt-6-9"><span class="woj">hallowed be your name,</span></span><br /><span id="en-NIV-23293" class="text Matt-6-10"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">10 </sup>your kingdom<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23293J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23293J'></sup> come,</span></span><br /><span class="text Matt-6-10"><span class="woj">your will be done,<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23293K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23293K'></sup></span></span><br /><span class="indent-1"><span class="indent-1-breaks">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span class="text Matt-6-10"><span class="woj">on earth as it is in heaven.</span></span></span><br /><span id="en-NIV-23294" class="text Matt-6-11"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">11 </sup>Give us today our daily bread.<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23294L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23294L'></sup></span></span><br /><span id="en-NIV-23295" class="text Matt-6-12"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">12 </sup>And forgive us our debts,</span></span><br /><span class="indent-1"><span class="indent-1-breaks">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span class="text Matt-6-12"><span class="woj">as we also have forgiven our debtors.<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23295M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23295M'></sup></span></span></span><br /><span id="en-NIV-23296" class="text Matt-6-13"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">13 </sup>And lead us not into temptation,<sup data-fn='#fen-NIV-23296a' class='footnote' data-link='[&lt;a href=&quot;#fen-NIV-23296a&quot; title=&quot;See footnote a&quot;&gt;a&lt;/a&gt;]'>[<a href="#fen-NIV-23296a" title="See footnote a">a</a>]</sup><sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23296N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23296N'></sup></span></span><br /><span class="indent-1"><span class="indent-1-breaks">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span class="text Matt-6-13"><span class="woj">but deliver us from the evil one.<sup data-fn='#fen-NIV-23296b' class='footnote' data-link='[&lt;a href=&quot;#fen-NIV-23296b&quot; title=&quot;See footnote b&quot;&gt;b&lt;/a&gt;]'>[<a href="#fen-NIV-23296b" title="See footnote b">b</a>]</sup>’<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23296O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23296O'></sup></span></span></span></p></div> <p class="first-line-none top-05"><span id="en-NIV-23297" class="text Matt-6-14"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">14 </sup>For if you forgive other people when they sin against you, your heavenly Father will also forgive you.<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23297P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23297P'></sup></span></span> <span id="en-NIV-23298" class="text Matt-6-15"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">15 </sup>But if you do not forgive others their sins, your Father will not forgive your sins.<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23298Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23298Q'></sup></span></span></p> <h3><span id="en-NIV-23299" class="text Matt-6-16">Fasting</span></h3><p><span class="text Matt-6-16"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">16 </sup>“When you fast,<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23299R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23299R'></sup> do not look somber<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23299S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23299S'></sup> as the hypocrites do, for they disfigure their faces to show others they are fasting. Truly I tell you, they have received their reward in full.</span></span> <span id="en-NIV-23300" class="text Matt-6-17"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">17 </sup>But when you fast, put oil on your head and wash your face,</span></span> <span id="en-NIV-23301" class="text Matt-6-18"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">18 </sup>so that it will not be obvious to others that you are fasting, but only to your Father, who is unseen; and your Father, who sees what is done in secret, will reward you.<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23301T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23301T'></sup></span></span></p> <h3><span id="en-NIV-23302" class="text Matt-6-19">Treasures in Heaven<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23302U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23302U'></sup></span></h3><p><span class="text Matt-6-19"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">19 </sup>“Do not store up for yourselves treasures on earth,<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23302V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23302V'></sup> where moths and vermin destroy,<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23302W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23302W'></sup> and where thieves break in and steal.</span></span> <span id="en-NIV-23303" class="text Matt-6-20"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">20 </sup>But store up for yourselves treasures in heaven,<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23303X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23303X'></sup> where moths and vermin do not destroy, and where thieves do not break in and steal.<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23303Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23303Y'></sup></span></span> <span id="en-NIV-23304" class="text Matt-6-21"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">21 </sup>For where your treasure is, there your heart will be also.<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23304Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23304Z'></sup></span></span></p> <p><span id="en-NIV-23305" class="text Matt-6-22"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">22 </sup>“The eye is the lamp of the body. If your eyes are healthy,<sup data-fn='#fen-NIV-23305c' class='footnote' data-link='[&lt;a href=&quot;#fen-NIV-23305c&quot; title=&quot;See footnote c&quot;&gt;c&lt;/a&gt;]'>[<a href="#fen-NIV-23305c" title="See footnote c">c</a>]</sup> your whole body will be full of light.</span></span> <span id="en-NIV-23306" class="text Matt-6-23"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">23 </sup>But if your eyes are unhealthy,<sup data-fn='#fen-NIV-23306d' class='footnote' data-link='[&lt;a href=&quot;#fen-NIV-23306d&quot; title=&quot;See footnote d&quot;&gt;d&lt;/a&gt;]'>[<a href="#fen-NIV-23306d" title="See footnote d">d</a>]</sup> your whole body will be full of darkness. If then the light within you is darkness, how great is that darkness!</span></span></p> <p><span id="en-NIV-23307" class="text Matt-6-24"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">24 </sup>“No one can serve two masters. Either you will hate the one and love the other, or you will be devoted to the one and despise the other. You cannot serve both God and money.<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23307AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23307AA'></sup></span></span></p> <h3><span id="en-NIV-23308" class="text Matt-6-25">Do Not Worry<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23308AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23308AB'></sup></span></h3><p><span class="text Matt-6-25"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">25 </sup>“Therefore I tell you, do not worry<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23308AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23308AC'></sup> about your life, what you will eat or drink; or about your body, what you will wear. Is not life more than food, and the body more than clothes?</span></span> <span id="en-NIV-23309" class="text Matt-6-26"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">26 </sup>Look at the birds of the air; they do not sow or reap or store away in barns, and yet your heavenly Father feeds them.<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23309AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23309AD'></sup> Are you not much more valuable than they?<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23309AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23309AE'></sup></span></span> <span id="en-NIV-23310" class="text Matt-6-27"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">27 </sup>Can any one of you by worrying add a single hour to your life<sup data-fn='#fen-NIV-23310e' class='footnote' data-link='[&lt;a href=&quot;#fen-NIV-23310e&quot; title=&quot;See footnote e&quot;&gt;e&lt;/a&gt;]'>[<a href="#fen-NIV-23310e" title="See footnote e">e</a>]</sup>?<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23310AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23310AF'></sup></span></span></p> <p><span id="en-NIV-23311" class="text Matt-6-28"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">28 </sup>“And why do you worry about clothes? See how the flowers of the field grow. They do not labor or spin.</span></span> <span id="en-NIV-23312" class="text Matt-6-29"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">29 </sup>Yet I tell you that not even Solomon in all his splendor<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23312AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23312AG'></sup> was dressed like one of these.</span></span> <span id="en-NIV-23313" class="text Matt-6-30"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">30 </sup>If that is how God clothes the grass of the field, which is here today and tomorrow is thrown into the fire, will he not much more clothe you—you of little faith?<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23313AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23313AH'></sup></span></span> <span id="en-NIV-23314" class="text Matt-6-31"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">31 </sup>So do not worry, saying, ‘What shall we eat?’ or ‘What shall we drink?’ or ‘What shall we wear?’</span></span> <span id="en-NIV-23315" class="text Matt-6-32"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">32 </sup>For the pagans run after all these things, and your heavenly Father knows that you need them.<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23315AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23315AI'></sup></span></span> <span id="en-NIV-23316" class="text Matt-6-33"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">33 </sup>But seek first his kingdom<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23316AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23316AJ'></sup> and his righteousness, and all these things will be given to you as well.<sup class='crossreference'  data-link='(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23316AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)' data-cr='#cen-NIV-23316AK'></sup></span></span> <span id="en-NIV-23317" class="text Matt-6-34"><span class="woj"><sup class="versenum">34 </sup>Therefore do not worry about tomorrow, for tomorrow will worry about itself. Each day has enough trouble of its own.</span></span></p> <div class="footnotes">
